sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch fail <code> <message>' command
# Terminal function that propagates exit codes from failed commands
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Must execute (not just display) to exit with preserved code
#   The _fail2 function outputs shell commands (printf + exit)
#
# Unlike 'error' which always exits 1, 'fail' preserves the exact exit code.
# This is used by the exit code propagation infrastructure to distinguish:
# - VPN-switch errors (exit 1 via error command)
# - External command failures (exit 127, 126, etc. via fail command)
#
# Step 1-2: Exit code propagation (producer-side failures)
#
